content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 17 ยง 8105.00 - General

State Regulations
(a) Route 34. Route
34 between the Cayuga/Tompkins county line and the Cayuga/Oswego county
line. (b) [Eff. until June 22, 1994, see also subd. (b) below.] Route 5. Route 5 between Route 34 and the

Cayuga-Seneca county line in the City of Auburn and Town of Aurelius. (b) [Eff. June 22, 1994 until Oct. 19, 1994, see also subd. (b) above and below.] Route 5. Route 5 between the Cayuga-Seneca
county line and the Auburn City/Sennett town line. (b) [Eff. Oct. 19, 1994, see also subd. (b)
above.] Route 5. Route 5 between the Cayuga-Seneca county line and the

Cayuga-Onondaga county line. (c) US
Route 20. US Route 20 between Route 5 in Auburn and the Cayuga/Onondaga county
line. (d) Route 104 between the

Wayne-Cayuga county line and the Cayuga-Oswego county line in the Towns of

Victory and Sterling. (e) [Eff. until Sept. 28, 1988, see also subd. (e) below.] Route 31. Route 31 between the

Seneca-Cayuga county line and Route 34 in the Towns of Montezuma, Mentz, and

Brutus and the Villages of Port Byron and Weedsport. (e) [Eff. Sept. 28, 1988, see also subd. (e)
above.] Route 31. Route 31 between the Seneca-Cayuga county line and the

Cayuga-Onondaga county line in the Towns of Montezuma, Mentz, Brutus, and the

Villages of Weedsport and Port Byron. (f) Route 90. Route 90 between Route 5 and

Gully Road in the Towns of Montezuma, Aurelius, Springport, and Ledyard and the

Village of Cayuga and Union Springs. Notes
